instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: How does EnergyPlus run time compare to the total time needed for an energy modeling job?
output: EnergyPlus run time is normally a small fraction of the total time needed to complete an energy modeling job.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is important to build up front in the EnergyPlus modeling process?
output: It is very important to build a clean and concise EnergyPlus model up front.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: When should techniques of simplifying large and complex building and systems be used?
output: Techniques of simplifying large and complex building and systems should be used during the creation of energy models especially during the early design process when detailed zoning and other information is not available.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What can take a significant amount of time during EnergyPlus runs?
output: Producing lots of hourly or sub-hourly reports from EnergyPlus runs can take a significant amount of time.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: When should modelers request time step reports?
output: Modelers should only request time step reports when necessary.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What type of reports take relatively small amounts of run time in EnergyPlus?
output: Producing summary reports and typical monthly reports take relatively small amounts of run time.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: Why are summary and typical monthly reports valuable?
output: These reports are valuable references for troubleshooting and model fine-tuning.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What should EnergyPlus modelers choose to use for improved performance?
output: EnergyPlus modelers should choose to use current available PCs with 3 or more GHz and 3 or more GB of RAM.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What can modelers do for a large volume of EnergyPlus parametric runs?
output: Modelers can launch multiple runs in parallel.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: Where do modelers spend most of their time during the EnergyPlus modeling process?
output: Most time is spent on troubleshooting and fine-tuning energy models.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is recommended during the early modeling process?
output: During the early modeling process it is recommended to keep the model as simple as possible and make quick runs to identify problems.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is the iterative process described in the EnergyPlus modeling tips?
output: The iterative process involves modifying the IDF file to fix problems and re-running the model until satisfactory solutions are found.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: Into how many phases can the simulation process be split?
output: The simulation process can be split into three phases: the diagnostic runs the preliminary runs and the final runs.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is the priority of the diagnostic runs in the simulation process?
output: The diagnostic runs prioritize speed over simulation accuracy.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What do diagnostic runs help identify?
output: The diagnostic runs help catch most model problems by running simulations on summer and winter design days.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is the purpose of the preliminary runs?
output: The preliminary runs use a tighter set of simulation settings to catch problems missed in the diagnostic runs and provide better results for quality assurance purposes.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What is the goal of the final runs in the simulation process?
output: The final runs use the EnergyPlus recommended set of simulation settings to achieve better accuracy for simulation results ready for review and reporting.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text
input: What should be done in the SimulationControl object for reducing run time?
output: In the SimulationControl object run simulation for sizing periods until everything is working well then switch to run simulation for weather file run periods.

instruction: Imagine you are a helpful assistant and building energy expert for the energyPlus Engineering Reference -> Chapter: Running EnergyPlus -> Section: Reducing Run Time Tips -> text

output: Turn off (comment them out in the text editor using !) daylighting controls while developing the HVAC simulation then turn back on for final runs.
